1
00:00:07,961 --> 00:00:09,621
<i><font color="#ffff00">Ra Mi-ran</font></i>

2
00:00:12,717 --> 00:00:16,868
<i><font color="#ffff00">Lee Do-hyun</font></i>

3
00:00:21,591 --> 00:00:23,681
<i><font color="#ffff00">Ahn Eun-jin</font></i>

4
00:00:23,705 --> 00:00:26,755
<i><font color="#ffff00">Yoo In-soo</font></i>

5
00:00:26,779 --> 00:00:29,592
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffff00">Sam-sik's Mill</font></i>

6
00:00:31,284 --> 00:00:33,607
<i><font color="#ffff00">Choi Moo-sung - Jung Woong-in - Hong Bi-ra</font></i>

7
00:00:34,024 --> 00:00:36,427
<i><font color="#ffff00">Seo Yi-sook - Jang Won-young - Kang Mal-geum</font></i>

8
00:00:41,077 --> 00:00:42,357
<i><font color="#ffff00">Kim Won-hae - Park Bo-kyung</font></i>

9
00:00:42,381 --> 00:00:44,434
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffff00">Happy Farm</font></i>

10
00:00:49,799 --> 00:00:54,971
<i><font color="#ffff00">The Good Bad Mother</font></i>

11
00:00:56,056 --> 00:00:57,491
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffff00">Oh Tae-soo</font></i>

12
00:00:57,515 --> 00:00:58,933
<i><font color="#ffff00">Final Episode</font></i>

13
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:04,105
<i><font color="#ffff00">I'll Be Taesocrates Dissatisfied
Rather Than a Pig Satisfied</font></i>

14
00:01:10,361 --> 00:01:12,214
{\an8}I'm surprised to see you.

15
00:01:12,238 --> 00:01:14,633
{\an8}I heard you were badly injured in an accident.

16
00:01:14,657 --> 00:01:16,177
{\an8}I was surprised too.

17
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:18,819
{\an8}I thought it was an accident.

18
00:01:18,912 --> 00:01:20,264
{\an8}But it turns out,

19
00:01:20,288 --> 00:01:22,239
{\an8}it wasn't an accident.

20
00:01:22,749 --> 00:01:27,104
{\an8}Just like how your mistress
Hwang Soo-hyun's corpse was discovered.

21
00:01:27,128 --> 00:01:28,314
{\an8}Are you here to...?

22
00:01:28,338 --> 00:01:29,872
{\an8}No.

23
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:35,127
{\an8}I wouldn't have bothered to
come here if I was coming after you.

24
00:01:35,386 --> 00:01:37,907
If a prosecutor were to
leak damaging information,

25
00:01:37,931 --> 00:01:40,382
your opposing party...

26
00:01:40,475 --> 00:01:41,660
No.

27
00:01:41,684 --> 00:01:44,038
This entire country would be bent...

28
00:01:44,062 --> 00:01:45,956
on taking you down.

29
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:47,416
Choi Kang-ho.

30
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:50,184
I'll be straightforward with you.

31
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:52,838
I only have one goal.

32
00:01:52,862 --> 00:01:54,590
It's to catch...

33
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:58,400
Chairman Song, the man who
murdered my father and attempted...

34
00:01:58,868 --> 00:02:01,403
to kill my mother and me.

35
00:02:05,041 --> 00:02:07,311
I want you to testify against him...

36
00:02:07,335 --> 00:02:09,939
regarding all his crimes and corrupt deeds...

37
00:02:09,963 --> 00:02:12,665
you swept under the rug.

38
00:02:13,341 --> 00:02:15,861
Then I won't disclose your crimes.

39
00:02:15,885 --> 00:02:17,279
What are you talking about?

40
00:02:17,303 --> 00:02:18,838
Oh Ha-young.

41
00:02:19,514 --> 00:02:21,882
She's with me right now.

42
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:40,302
Her resentment and hatred
for you seems quite deep.

43
00:02:40,326 --> 00:02:42,847
If you refuse to testify,

44
00:02:42,871 --> 00:02:45,739
then Ha-young will take the stand instead.

45
00:02:46,207 --> 00:02:49,285
I'm not asking you for a favor.

46
00:02:50,336 --> 00:02:52,454
I'm giving you a chance.

47
00:02:55,842 --> 00:02:57,835
So what will it be?

48
00:02:59,429 --> 00:03:02,074
Will you take down Song Woo-byeok with me,

49
00:03:02,098 --> 00:03:04,451
and become President?

50
00:03:04,475 --> 00:03:06,495
Or will you side with him...

51
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:08,971
and go to hell together?

52
00:03:11,316 --> 00:03:14,944
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffff00">The Good Bad Mother</font></i>

53
00:03:15,778 --> 00:03:19,174
Goodness, you're working hard night and day.

54
00:03:19,198 --> 00:03:21,969
Is our food here yet?

55
00:03:21,993 --> 00:03:24,846
<i><font color="#ffff00">Hotel Captain</font></i>

56
00:03:25,371 --> 00:03:28,115
Why did you put it back here?

57
00:03:30,126 --> 00:03:32,563
- What are you doing?
- My gosh, you startled me!

58
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:35,024
What are you doing to our food?

59
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:36,066
Give it to me!

60
00:03:36,090 --> 00:03:38,611
I was just curious about...

61
00:03:38,635 --> 00:03:41,447
what people at the Prosecutors'
Office have for a meal.

62
00:03:41,471 --> 00:03:45,424
But I guess they're no different from us.

63
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:47,286
Don't tell me...

64
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:50,122
you spiked our food.

65
00:03:50,146 --> 00:03:51,582
Hey.

66
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:55,044
Do you think it's that easy to get drugs?

67
00:03:55,068 --> 00:03:57,880
I'd rather spend that money
on buying myself supplements.

68
00:03:57,904 --> 00:04:00,424
I haven't slept well since you guys arrived.

69
00:04:00,448 --> 00:04:02,134
Look at how haggard I am.

70
00:04:02,158 --> 00:04:03,886
Can you tell?

71
00:04:03,910 --> 00:04:05,930
You should just quit drinking.

72
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:07,655
Sam-sik.

73
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:09,531
By the way,

74
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:13,854
is this what people call an office romance?

75
00:04:13,878 --> 00:04:16,580
What are you talking about? What romance?

76
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:22,378
The prosecutor and his investigation officer.

77
00:04:23,596 --> 00:04:27,925
They're on fire!

78
00:04:30,895 --> 00:04:32,373
Why are you crying?

79
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:37,253
Next, tell me what you and your dad
talked about on the day of the accident.

80
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:39,713
I'm not sure about this.

81
00:04:39,737 --> 00:04:41,465
What? What do you mean?

82
00:04:41,489 --> 00:04:44,400
Even if I claim he made me do it,

83
00:04:44,909 --> 00:04:46,860
I have no evidence.

84
00:04:46,911 --> 00:04:49,655
Then I'll end up taking all the blame.

85
00:04:52,542 --> 00:04:55,479
I know I should pay for what I've done.

86
00:04:55,503 --> 00:04:58,622
But I'm afraid I may not be of any help...

87
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:01,375
to Kang-ho.

88
00:05:02,802 --> 00:05:05,781
You're already helping him greatly...

89
00:05:05,805 --> 00:05:08,215
by doing this.

90
00:05:09,142 --> 00:05:11,287
He said he'll find evidence,

91
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:13,303
so let's trust him and wait.

92
00:05:25,199 --> 00:05:29,972
<i>Song Woo-byeok has ties with
the prosecution and the court.</i>

93
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:32,698
<i>So it won't be easy to get a warrant.</i>

94
00:05:32,790 --> 00:05:36,869
If you attack him without being fully prepared,

95
00:05:37,503 --> 00:05:40,164
he'll catch on to your plan.

96
00:05:40,298 --> 00:05:42,833
<i>And that'll put everyone in danger.</i>

97
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:45,362
When will you return from the U.S.?

98
00:05:45,386 --> 00:05:47,573
If I could,

99
00:05:47,597 --> 00:05:50,743
I'd love to stay and watch the
World Series before coming back.

100
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:54,872
Are you saying you'll neglect
the Woobyeok Beasts this season?

101
00:05:54,896 --> 00:05:56,430
You're right.

102
00:05:56,939 --> 00:06:01,101
I must be getting senile.

103
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:10,554
My goodness.

104
00:06:10,578 --> 00:06:13,447
What a killer view.

105
00:06:13,748 --> 00:06:17,618
I get to see this thanks to you.

106
00:06:19,253 --> 00:06:20,913
By the way,

107
00:06:21,714 --> 00:06:23,582
why are you here alone?

108
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:25,834
Did you have to do that?

109
00:06:26,636 --> 00:06:29,004
I devoted my entire life...

110
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:30,783
to serving you, sir.

111
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:33,425
Did you really have to try to kill me?

112
00:06:33,601 --> 00:06:35,344
What are you...?

113
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:42,002
Are you crying?

114
00:06:42,026 --> 00:06:45,339
A grown man crying is embarrassing.

115
00:06:45,363 --> 00:06:48,273
Sir, we should get going.

116
00:06:52,787 --> 00:06:54,056
Hey.

117
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:56,642
If you made it out alive,

118
00:06:56,666 --> 00:07:00,395
you should've fled to
another country to survive.

119
00:07:00,419 --> 00:07:04,358
Why would you come back here
and drive a nail into your coffin?

120
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:07,027
In any case, I want to thank you.

121
00:07:07,051 --> 00:07:10,671
When I heard you were still alive,

122
00:07:10,847 --> 00:07:13,367
I was hesitant about
going on this business trip.

123
00:07:13,391 --> 00:07:16,385
But now I can leave at ease.

124
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:19,388
Goodbye, then.

125
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:25,185
You asked why I came alone.

126
00:07:28,030 --> 00:07:31,635
Mr. Cha will hear everything you just said.

127
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:33,095
One of us...

128
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:35,931
must stay alive to expose you.

129
00:07:35,955 --> 00:07:38,767
You douchebag!

130
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:40,644
You were crying all this time,

131
00:07:40,668 --> 00:07:42,604
and you start bargaining with me...

132
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:46,248
when it's almost time for my flight, you jerk?

133
00:07:51,679 --> 00:07:53,532
What do you want?

134
00:07:53,556 --> 00:07:55,951
Tell me! You'll be dead soon enough.

135
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:58,245
Do you need a home? Or money?

136
00:07:58,269 --> 00:08:01,415
Do you want me to adopt
you as I did with Kang-ho?

137
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:05,058
I had the opportunity to farm thanks to you.

138
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:08,645
Interestingly enough,
I reaped everything I sowed.

139
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:11,773
You'll also reap what you've sown.

140
00:08:12,158 --> 00:08:13,802
How dare you?

141
00:08:13,826 --> 00:08:16,054
Die, you douchebag!

142
00:08:16,078 --> 00:08:18,405
- Chairman Song.
- What?

143
00:08:29,175 --> 00:08:30,751
Kang-ho.

144
00:08:33,763 --> 00:08:35,073
You're alive?

145
00:08:35,097 --> 00:08:36,450
My goodness.

146
00:08:36,474 --> 00:08:39,551
I don't care about anything else.

147
00:08:40,144 --> 00:08:42,971
I'm completely fine as long as I have you.

148
00:08:45,816 --> 00:08:47,252
I'm sorry.

149
00:08:47,276 --> 00:08:49,269
But I've only just begun.

150
00:08:49,987 --> 00:08:51,730
Song Woo-byeok.

151
00:08:52,865 --> 00:08:55,219
You're under arrest for special assault...

152
00:08:55,243 --> 00:08:56,637
and attempted murder.

153
00:08:56,661 --> 00:08:57,804
What are you doing?

154
00:08:57,828 --> 00:08:59,723
You have the right to remain silent.

155
00:08:59,747 --> 00:09:02,935
Anything you say can and will be
used against you in a court of law.

156
00:09:02,959 --> 00:09:04,228
Kang-ho.

157
00:09:04,252 --> 00:09:06,078
Will you be okay?

158
00:09:06,671 --> 00:09:08,830
Please don't skip your meals.

159
00:09:10,466 --> 00:09:12,209
Take him.

160
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:27,083
<i><font color="#ffa07a">So</font></i>

161
00:09:28,943 --> 00:09:30,462
Hello?

162
00:09:30,486 --> 00:09:32,464
- <i>Hey.</i>
- Let me talk to Choi Kang-ho.

163
00:09:32,488 --> 00:09:34,258
Kang-ho?

164
00:09:34,282 --> 00:09:35,300
Kang...

165
00:09:35,324 --> 00:09:37,234
Hold on.

166
00:09:38,869 --> 00:09:40,654
It's for you.

167
00:09:42,164 --> 00:09:44,685
- Hello?
- <i>Choi Kang-ho.</i>

168
00:09:44,709 --> 00:09:46,285
Run away.

169
00:09:46,335 --> 00:09:48,480
It'll be difficult to obtain
an arrest warrant...

170
00:09:48,504 --> 00:09:50,315
for Chairman Song's past crimes.

171
00:09:50,339 --> 00:09:53,250
That only leaves us with one option.

172
00:09:53,801 --> 00:09:56,238
We need to catch him red-handed.

173
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:59,825
But I heard he'll be going
on a business trip to the U.S.

174
00:09:59,849 --> 00:10:01,159
When is that?

175
00:10:01,183 --> 00:10:02,869
Here's the plan.

176
00:10:02,893 --> 00:10:05,998
Once I get to the rooftop, I'd
like for you all to accompany me,

177
00:10:06,022 --> 00:10:08,675
and carry out a search-and-seizure
of Woobyeok Group. Got it?

178
00:10:08,699 --> 00:10:09,876
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

179
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:12,769
Now that he's back, I'm motivated to work hard.

180
00:10:21,662 --> 00:10:24,266
Recently a victim claimed to
have received death threats...

181
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:27,290
from Chairman Song Woo-byeok, and
thus we conducted an investigation.

182
00:10:27,314 --> 00:10:28,478
And yesterday at 2 p.m.,

183
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:30,063
we arrested him at the scene...

184
00:10:30,087 --> 00:10:32,316
at Woobyeok Group's headquarters,

185
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:35,876
after he assaulted again and
attempted to murder the victim.

186
00:10:36,552 --> 00:10:40,115
Since the suspect attempted
to destroy the victim's phone...

187
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:42,826
and was due to fly out to the U.S.,

188
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:45,996
we deemed it likely that he might
try to destroy evidence and flee.

189
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:48,332
<i>How will you carry out this investigation?</i>

190
00:10:48,356 --> 00:10:50,000
- Sir.
- <i>A civil servant...</i>

191
00:10:50,024 --> 00:10:53,545
<i>must be impartial when serving the country.</i>

192
00:10:53,569 --> 00:10:57,049
<i>As per the Prosecutor General's
words to carry out fair investigations,</i>

193
00:10:57,073 --> 00:10:59,176
<i>even against the powerful,</i>

194
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:03,680
we'll carry out an honest,
transparent, and thorough investigation.

195
00:11:03,704 --> 00:11:08,075
- What's the victim's current state?
- Did the suspect admit to the charges?

196
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:18,362
Sir.

197
00:11:18,386 --> 00:11:20,712
It's me, Oh Tae-soo.

198
00:11:21,514 --> 00:11:24,785
Young-soon, hurry up. It's starting.

199
00:11:24,809 --> 00:11:26,510
Coming.

200
00:11:28,562 --> 00:11:31,875
♫ <i>When did you enter my heart</i> ♫

201
00:11:31,899 --> 00:11:34,002
♫ <i>and make me fall in love?</i> ♫

202
00:11:34,026 --> 00:11:35,670
Come on.

203
00:11:35,694 --> 00:11:38,298
- <i>You're...</i>
- My babies.

204
00:11:38,322 --> 00:11:40,357
I brought you some snacks.

205
00:11:41,659 --> 00:11:43,053
Sweet potatoes again.

206
00:11:43,077 --> 00:11:45,055
You don't like sweet potatoes?

207
00:11:45,079 --> 00:11:46,932
Do you want mung bean pancakes?

208
00:11:46,956 --> 00:11:49,810
- That's enough.
- Come here.

209
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:51,478
Can we please just watch?

210
00:11:51,502 --> 00:11:55,148
Is that the song that Mr. Baek wrote?

211
00:11:55,172 --> 00:11:56,483
That's right.

212
00:11:56,507 --> 00:12:01,336
Apparently the song is very popular
now. What was the title again?

213
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:06,535
- "Intrusion into My Heart."
- That's right.

214
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:08,662
- Come here.
- Goodness.

215
00:12:08,686 --> 00:12:10,205
How nice!

216
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:12,374
You're blocking the TV.

217
00:12:12,398 --> 00:12:14,000
This is great!

218
00:12:14,024 --> 00:12:16,211
Let us watch the TV.

219
00:12:16,235 --> 00:12:17,894
Hold on.

220
00:12:18,404 --> 00:12:20,882
Move aside! You're blocking the TV.

221
00:12:20,906 --> 00:12:22,384
- What?
- What is it?

222
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:24,302
- What is that?
- What is that?

223
00:12:24,326 --> 00:12:27,055
Song Woo-byeok from Woobyeok Group was arrested?

224
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:28,348
What?

225
00:12:28,372 --> 00:12:31,286
<i>Chairman Song has allegedly engaged
in assault and death threats...</i>

226
00:12:31,310 --> 00:12:32,602
{\an8}<i>prior to this incident.</i>

227
00:12:32,626 --> 00:12:36,690
{\an8}<i>People are in an uproar after learning
that there have been many victims.</i>

228
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:39,280
<i>Recently a victim claimed to
have received death threats...</i>

229
00:12:39,304 --> 00:12:42,304
{\an8}<i>from Chairman Song Woo-byeok,
and thus we conducted an investigation.</i>

230
00:12:42,328 --> 00:12:44,212
What am I looking at?

231
00:12:44,472 --> 00:12:46,214
Is that Kang-ho?

232
00:12:46,891 --> 00:12:50,302
Can you slap me?

233
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:55,667
It's him.

234
00:12:55,691 --> 00:12:58,211
It hurts, so that must be Kang-ho.

235
00:12:58,235 --> 00:13:00,687
It hurts, so that's Kang-ho!

236
00:13:00,946 --> 00:13:02,132
Our son...

237
00:13:02,156 --> 00:13:04,009
Kang-ho is back!

238
00:13:04,033 --> 00:13:05,552
Kang-ho!

239
00:13:05,576 --> 00:13:07,554
That's Sam-sik's best friend,

240
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:10,265
Kang-ho!

241
00:13:10,289 --> 00:13:11,892
What is this?

242
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:14,826
Why didn't you tell me?

243
00:13:14,919 --> 00:13:17,162
You didn't trust me?

244
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:19,191
Answer me!

245
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:20,317
We're in-laws!

246
00:13:20,341 --> 00:13:22,152
- What?
- What?

247
00:13:22,176 --> 00:13:24,154
- "In-laws"?
- With who?

248
00:13:24,178 --> 00:13:26,421
With me!

249
00:13:27,348 --> 00:13:30,258
Right, Mother?

250
00:13:32,311 --> 00:13:33,955
How about...

251
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:36,625
we all visit Seoul together?

252
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:39,544
- Sure!
- We must!

253
00:13:39,568 --> 00:13:41,269
Let's go!

254
00:13:41,737 --> 00:13:43,340
Is your seat belt on?

255
00:13:43,364 --> 00:13:45,133
Do you like fish?

256
00:13:45,157 --> 00:13:47,344
Feel free to rest your head on this.

257
00:13:47,368 --> 00:13:49,110
Move.

258
00:13:49,828 --> 00:13:51,723
We could've gone by ourselves.

259
00:13:51,747 --> 00:13:53,225
Why is he here?

260
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:54,267
Shut it.

261
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:57,354
If something happens to you
on the way, he'll suspect me.

262
00:13:57,378 --> 00:13:58,688
Easy on the brakes.

263
00:13:58,712 --> 00:14:00,815
I just had them replaced.

264
00:14:00,839 --> 00:14:04,110
I bought this car to drive
to the award ceremony.

265
00:14:04,134 --> 00:14:07,322
It fits five people perfectly.

266
00:14:07,346 --> 00:14:08,782
You're right.

267
00:14:08,806 --> 00:14:11,952
Gum-ja must've become a widow for this very day.

268
00:14:11,976 --> 00:14:13,078
What did you say?

269
00:14:13,102 --> 00:14:15,372
I'll buy a bigger car soon,

270
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:17,457
so let's go again another time.

271
00:14:17,481 --> 00:14:18,375
That sounds great!

272
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:20,752
Your son is still considered a suspect.

273
00:14:20,776 --> 00:14:23,353
We still have an eye on him.

274
00:14:23,529 --> 00:14:24,840
I don't want to hear it.

275
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:26,967
Just keep your eyes on the road.

276
00:14:26,991 --> 00:14:28,775
Yes, ma'am.

277
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:34,224
<i>Honey.</i>

278
00:14:34,248 --> 00:14:36,283
<i>Are you watching from above?</i>

279
00:14:37,209 --> 00:14:39,452
<i>The day has finally come.</i>

280
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:47,168
<i>Our son will carry out the judgment...</i>

281
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:51,548
<i>we failed to do.</i>

282
00:14:57,730 --> 00:15:00,473
<i>Please help him stay strong.</i>

283
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:05,088
<i>Please help him not to doubt, falter,</i>

284
00:15:05,112 --> 00:15:07,689
<i>or be intimidated.</i>

285
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:10,817
<i>Let him stay strong.</i>

286
00:15:14,496 --> 00:15:16,496
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffff00">Prosecutor</font></i>

287
00:15:22,046 --> 00:15:24,024
<i>Help him look them in the eye...</i>

288
00:15:24,048 --> 00:15:25,942
{\an8}<i>and state the truth.</i>

289
00:15:25,966 --> 00:15:27,736
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffff00">Defendant</font></i>

290
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:30,253
{\an8}<i>Just like how you did...</i>

291
00:15:30,387 --> 00:15:32,964
<i>in front of them,</i>

292
00:15:33,098 --> 00:15:35,619
<i>please help Kang-ho...</i>

293
00:15:35,643 --> 00:15:38,845
<i>remain confident...</i>

294
00:15:39,229 --> 00:15:41,431
<i>until the end.</i>

295
00:15:41,982 --> 00:15:44,225
All rise.

296
00:15:47,696 --> 00:15:49,856
<i>With sincerity,</i>

297
00:15:50,282 --> 00:15:52,484
<i>resentment,</i>

298
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:55,904
<i>and desperation...</i>

299
00:15:57,414 --> 00:15:59,240
<i>I pray to you.</i>

300
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:02,744
You may be seated.

301
00:16:03,879 --> 00:16:07,233
{\an8}Case 133 of the year 2023.

302
00:16:07,257 --> 00:16:09,626
We'll now begin the trial.

303
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:15,116
The assault that occurred
in Jou-ri on January 20...

304
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:17,619
was just a simple fight between colleagues...

305
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:19,371
{\an8}over their pecking order.

306
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:21,915
{\an8}Soh Ji-seok's claim that
Chairman Song Woo-byeok...

307
00:16:21,939 --> 00:16:25,335
{\an8}ordered an assault to be
carried out is completely false.

308
00:16:25,359 --> 00:16:27,420
{\an8}The recent incident transpired...

309
00:16:27,444 --> 00:16:29,923
{\an8}due to Mr. Soh's attacking Chairman Song.

310
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:31,800
And the latter...

311
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:34,734
simply reacted to defend himself.

312
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:40,141
Did you just say that the
victim attacked the defendant?

313
00:16:40,165 --> 00:16:42,617
{\an8}Are you talking about this?

314
00:16:43,419 --> 00:16:45,078
Please play it.

315
00:16:46,964 --> 00:16:50,235
<i>Mr. Cha will hear everything you just said.</i>

316
00:16:50,259 --> 00:16:52,028
{\an8}<i>One of us...</i>

317
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:54,906
<i>must stay alive to expose you.</i>

318
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:57,701
- <i>You douchebag!</i>
- What is that?

319
00:16:57,725 --> 00:16:59,703
<i>You were crying all this time,</i>

320
00:16:59,727 --> 00:17:01,788
{\an8}<i>and you start bargaining with me...</i>

321
00:17:01,812 --> 00:17:04,666
<i>when it's almost time for my flight, jerk?</i>

322
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:06,725
I'll submit this as evidence.

323
00:17:09,236 --> 00:17:13,299
{\an8}I'd like to question the victim who's
also the witness to that incident.

324
00:17:13,323 --> 00:17:18,138
After the assault in Jou-ri, you
came to me for help and claimed...

325
00:17:18,162 --> 00:17:22,100
that the defendant was trying
to murder you. Is this correct?

326
00:17:22,124 --> 00:17:23,018
Yes.

327
00:17:23,042 --> 00:17:25,854
Why did he want to kill you?

328
00:17:25,878 --> 00:17:29,733
Because as his trusted secretary,

329
00:17:29,757 --> 00:17:32,902
I had a great deal of
information about his actions.

330
00:17:32,926 --> 00:17:36,281
{\an8}The defendant spent about 30 years as the CEO...

331
00:17:36,305 --> 00:17:39,075
of Yongra Construction and Woobyeok Group.

332
00:17:39,099 --> 00:17:42,328
He must've had many employees
who worked closely with him,

333
00:17:42,352 --> 00:17:46,041
and they must've known a
lot of private information too.

334
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:48,933
Are you telling me they're all dead?

335
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:54,814
Yes.

336
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,343
Objection, Your Honor.

337
00:17:57,367 --> 00:18:01,139
- It hasn't been verified...
- Right, so I verified his claim.

338
00:18:01,163 --> 00:18:02,640
In the past 30 years,

339
00:18:02,664 --> 00:18:05,060
the defendant had four other secretaries...

340
00:18:05,084 --> 00:18:07,103
who worked closely with him.

341
00:18:07,127 --> 00:18:10,523
Two committed suicide
and one died in a car crash.

342
00:18:10,547 --> 00:18:15,084
And the last secretary's body was
recently found near Jemyeon Island.

343
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:18,031
It was Hwang Soo-hyun.

344
00:18:18,055 --> 00:18:21,284
{\an8}Your Honor, the prosecution is
referring to a case that's irrelevant to...

345
00:18:21,308 --> 00:18:24,079
I'm verifying the witness' statement.

346
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:26,137
How is that irrelevant?

347
00:18:27,397 --> 00:18:28,932
Prosecution.

348
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:30,850
You may continue.

349
00:18:32,236 --> 00:18:33,895
That's right.

350
00:18:34,029 --> 00:18:36,216
This USB was found at the defendant's office...

351
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:39,067
during a search-and-seizure.

352
00:18:39,493 --> 00:18:41,012
Do you know what it contains?

353
00:18:41,036 --> 00:18:44,390
It contains confidential documents
related to Woobyeok's corrupt deeds,

354
00:18:44,414 --> 00:18:48,603
Chairman Song's double bookkeeping,
breach of trust, and embezzlement.

355
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:50,647
It belonged to Hwang Soo-hyun.

356
00:18:50,671 --> 00:18:52,357
What's he talking about?

357
00:18:52,381 --> 00:18:54,082
Hwang Soo-hyun?

358
00:18:55,008 --> 00:18:57,362
Could you explain this video...

359
00:18:57,386 --> 00:19:00,657
found on your secretary's laptop?

360
00:19:00,681 --> 00:19:02,298
Please play it.

361
00:19:02,391 --> 00:19:04,119
<i>Don't be ridiculous.</i>

362
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:08,555
<i>I already know the hit-and-run accident
and suicide were in the contract.</i>

363
00:19:10,774 --> 00:19:14,879
A year ago, Chairman Song ordered
me to visit Yang Gu-man's wife,

364
00:19:14,903 --> 00:19:16,589
and retrieve his money.

365
00:19:16,613 --> 00:19:18,690
Gosh.

366
00:19:19,116 --> 00:19:21,469
All right. Then I'd like to ask the defendant.

367
00:19:21,493 --> 00:19:23,388
According to the investigation,

368
00:19:23,412 --> 00:19:26,266
Hwang Soo-hyun was last seen before her death...

369
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:28,741
on October 3, 2021.

370
00:19:28,792 --> 00:19:32,147
It's the same day the last
video on this USB was saved.

371
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:35,206
So why was this USB found in your desk?

372
00:19:40,053 --> 00:19:41,322
Look.

373
00:19:41,346 --> 00:19:44,409
How would I know anything
about the USB or that Mr. Yang,

374
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:47,620
when he's the one who schemed everything?

375
00:19:47,644 --> 00:19:51,583
So you're claiming that the
victim schemed everything himself,

376
00:19:51,607 --> 00:19:55,628
and you never murdered or abetted murder?

377
00:19:55,652 --> 00:19:56,671
Correct.

378
00:19:56,695 --> 00:19:58,646
That's a lie!

379
00:19:58,822 --> 00:20:02,567
He also ordered me to kill people.

380
00:20:04,912 --> 00:20:07,265
He ordered you to kill people?

381
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:08,600
Who were they?

382
00:20:08,624 --> 00:20:11,728
Jung Jong-gu, the defendant
in the murder case...

383
00:20:11,752 --> 00:20:13,938
that Chairman Song's grandson was involved in,

384
00:20:13,962 --> 00:20:18,791
and Park Cheol-su, the defendant in
the Woobyeok construction site case.

385
00:20:19,259 --> 00:20:20,904
So did you carry out your orders?

386
00:20:20,928 --> 00:20:23,573
They were both incarcerated,

387
00:20:23,597 --> 00:20:25,632
so I couldn't.

388
00:20:28,268 --> 00:20:32,624
I found a few odd things
during this investigation.

389
00:20:32,648 --> 00:20:34,307
It's the fact that...

390
00:20:34,483 --> 00:20:38,213
not only the defendant's
secretaries, but also many of those...

391
00:20:38,237 --> 00:20:41,216
who raised suspicions about
the defendant or his company,

392
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:44,302
or were involved in the trials,

393
00:20:44,326 --> 00:20:48,139
suddenly passed away or disappeared.

394
00:20:48,163 --> 00:20:52,060
Objection, Your Honor. The
prosecution is distorting the truth...

395
00:20:52,084 --> 00:20:53,811
solely based on the victim's claims.

396
00:20:53,835 --> 00:20:58,039
Then let me summon another
witness who can verify this.

397
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:15,917
Approved.

398
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:17,961
Witness, Mr. Oh Tae-soo,

399
00:21:17,985 --> 00:21:19,811
please come forward.

400
00:21:22,447 --> 00:21:23,591
Oh Tae-soo?

401
00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:25,608
Oh Tae-soo?

402
00:21:44,886 --> 00:21:46,155
What is this?

403
00:21:46,179 --> 00:21:48,589
Why is he testifying?

404
00:21:53,729 --> 00:21:55,456
"I pledge this."

405
00:21:55,480 --> 00:22:00,044
"I solemnly swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth, and nothing but the truth,"

406
00:22:00,068 --> 00:22:01,504
"and agree to be punished..."

407
00:22:01,528 --> 00:22:04,094
"in accordance with perjury
should there be any falsehood."

408
00:22:04,118 --> 00:22:06,486
"Witness, Oh Tae-soo."

409
00:22:06,742 --> 00:22:08,428
If Song Woo-byeok is arrested,

410
00:22:08,452 --> 00:22:12,280
Bareun Hanguk Party, the political and
business worlds, and even the media...

411
00:22:12,831 --> 00:22:15,074
will find fault with you.

412
00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:17,562
Because everyone knows about...

413
00:22:17,586 --> 00:22:20,580
your secret ties with him
and how far they go back.

414
00:22:23,091 --> 00:22:25,543
But what if...

415
00:22:26,344 --> 00:22:28,546
you testify against him?

416
00:22:29,389 --> 00:22:33,718
It'd be a perfect chance to
dispel all the suspicions...

417
00:22:33,977 --> 00:22:38,124
regarding the relationship between you and him.

418
00:22:38,148 --> 00:22:41,878
{\an8}You have indicted Chairman Song many times...

419
00:22:41,902 --> 00:22:44,255
for 30 years since 1987.

420
00:22:44,279 --> 00:22:46,632
- Is this true?
- Correct.

421
00:22:46,656 --> 00:22:49,427
However, most of these
indictments were dismissed.

422
00:22:49,451 --> 00:22:52,972
The majority of these cases,
13 in total, were dismissed...

423
00:22:52,996 --> 00:22:55,490
due to the victims' deaths.

424
00:22:55,582 --> 00:22:57,018
{\an8}That's correct.

425
00:22:57,042 --> 00:22:59,187
Did you ever find the repeated deaths...

426
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:02,705
of the plaintiffs or victims rather odd?

427
00:23:04,466 --> 00:23:07,904
{\an8}There was no issue in the
investigation of their deaths,

428
00:23:07,928 --> 00:23:11,074
and the bereaved families
didn't raise any suspicion.

429
00:23:11,098 --> 00:23:14,008
So I didn't find them particularly odd.

430
00:23:16,019 --> 00:23:18,706
However, I found something odd...

431
00:23:18,730 --> 00:23:21,974
in this trial.

432
00:23:22,234 --> 00:23:24,587
It's the death of Hwang Soo-hyun,

433
00:23:24,611 --> 00:23:27,188
his secretary.

434
00:23:27,781 --> 00:23:30,718
{\an8}She worked as my secretary...

435
00:23:30,742 --> 00:23:33,971
{\an8}from 2018 to 2020.

436
00:23:33,995 --> 00:23:35,890
Then one day in 2020,

437
00:23:35,914 --> 00:23:39,617
she told me she wanted to quit.

438
00:23:39,918 --> 00:23:41,536
The reason being...

439
00:23:43,130 --> 00:23:45,915
that getting pregnant
had put her life in danger.

440
00:23:50,428 --> 00:23:53,116
Her pregnancy had put her life in danger?

441
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:54,715
Correct.

442
00:23:55,392 --> 00:23:58,135
{\an8}She said Chairman Song was the father.

443
00:24:05,026 --> 00:24:07,088
If you do this,

444
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:08,881
all the disgusting work...

445
00:24:08,905 --> 00:24:13,302
I forced myself to put up with will go to waste.

446
00:24:13,326 --> 00:24:16,347
I was even willing to serve time in jail...

447
00:24:16,371 --> 00:24:19,058
to make you become President,

448
00:24:19,082 --> 00:24:20,685
you douchebag!

449
00:24:20,709 --> 00:24:22,353
Defendant, please sit down!

450
00:24:22,377 --> 00:24:24,480
How is that baby mine?

451
00:24:24,504 --> 00:24:27,650
Like killing that poor baby wasn't enough,

452
00:24:27,674 --> 00:24:31,028
{\an8}are you trying to turn him into a jerk now?

453
00:24:31,052 --> 00:24:32,530
{\an8}You even plotted...

454
00:24:32,554 --> 00:24:34,866
to kill Choi Kang-ho with your daughter!

455
00:24:34,890 --> 00:24:36,826
- You douchebag!
- Defendant!

456
00:24:36,850 --> 00:24:39,198
- How dare you utter such nonsense?
- Please calm down!

457
00:24:39,222 --> 00:24:42,096
You douchebag! I'm not going down.

458
00:24:42,230 --> 00:24:45,793
<i>No, not yet, Honey.</i>

459
00:24:45,817 --> 00:24:49,338
<i>If I waver right now, our son will waver too.</i>

460
00:24:49,362 --> 00:24:52,341
<i>Everything he's done up to now will be ruined.</i>

461
00:24:52,365 --> 00:24:54,218
<i>Please, Honey.</i>

462
00:24:54,242 --> 00:24:56,387
<i>Keep me here for a little longer.</i>

463
00:24:56,411 --> 00:24:58,181
<i>Please...</i>

464
00:24:58,205 --> 00:24:59,849
<i>Just a little longer.</i>

465
00:24:59,873 --> 00:25:00,850
Sit down!

466
00:25:00,874 --> 00:25:03,811
- Sir. Please.
- I ought to kill you.

467
00:25:03,835 --> 00:25:05,411
Darn it!

468
00:25:12,260 --> 00:25:13,878
It's true.

469
00:25:15,639 --> 00:25:17,673
I slipped...

470
00:25:18,141 --> 00:25:21,344
{\an8}Prosecutor Choi Kang-ho sleeping pills.

471
00:25:33,990 --> 00:25:36,052
{\an8}We'll accept the prosecutor's request.

472
00:25:36,076 --> 00:25:39,805
{\an8}We believe verifying the facts
is of the utmost importance.

473
00:25:39,829 --> 00:25:43,658
You may cross-examine the two witnesses.

474
00:25:45,961 --> 00:25:49,649
{\an8}I was deceived into believing that
Prosecutor Choi, my then fiancée,

475
00:25:49,673 --> 00:25:51,958
had another woman and a baby.

476
00:25:52,175 --> 00:25:54,862
And that he even killed them...

477
00:25:54,886 --> 00:25:57,254
so he could marry me.

478
00:25:57,764 --> 00:26:00,534
Who told you that?

479
00:26:00,558 --> 00:26:01,911
It was my father,

480
00:26:01,935 --> 00:26:04,095
Assemblyman Oh Tae-soo.

481
00:26:09,442 --> 00:26:11,936
It's all my fault.

482
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:17,566
I've been threatened by Chairman Song
ever since I decided to run for President.

483
00:26:17,909 --> 00:26:21,737
He wanted me to protect his corrupt company...

484
00:26:21,788 --> 00:26:24,782
and himself.

485
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:28,354
When I refused, he attempted
to use my daughter...

486
00:26:28,378 --> 00:26:31,080
to get rid of Prosecutor Choi.

487
00:26:31,548 --> 00:26:34,694
Why did Chairman Song want me dead?

488
00:26:34,718 --> 00:26:38,879
That's because 35 years ago, Chairman Song...

489
00:26:39,889 --> 00:26:43,259
murdered Prosecutor Choi's father.

490
00:26:44,644 --> 00:26:46,637
Is that true?

491
00:26:50,150 --> 00:26:51,502
Simply put,

492
00:26:51,526 --> 00:26:55,256
there were two people Chairman
Song needed to get rid of.

493
00:26:55,280 --> 00:26:56,841
Hwang Soo-hyun, his mistress,

494
00:26:56,865 --> 00:27:00,443
and Choi Kang-ho, Choi Hae-sik's son.

495
00:27:00,994 --> 00:27:02,388
That's why he killed her,

496
00:27:02,412 --> 00:27:04,682
and framed Prosecutor Choi for it.

497
00:27:04,706 --> 00:27:08,686
And after that, he ordered my
daughter to kill Prosecutor Choi.

498
00:27:08,710 --> 00:27:10,786
Stop lying.

499
00:27:14,299 --> 00:27:17,543
It was you who wanted him dead.

500
00:27:19,137 --> 00:27:21,699
It was also you who killed
Hwang Soo-hyun and her baby.

501
00:27:21,723 --> 00:27:24,967
They were your mistress and son.

502
00:27:28,563 --> 00:27:31,098
I saw the DNA test result...

503
00:27:31,191 --> 00:27:33,809
with my own eyes.

504
00:27:44,746 --> 00:27:48,282
This is my daughter's medical
record from the mental hospital.

505
00:27:49,751 --> 00:27:51,452
That's right.

506
00:27:51,961 --> 00:27:55,164
My daughter isn't sane.

507
00:27:55,590 --> 00:27:57,416
I've been hiding it...

508
00:27:58,009 --> 00:28:01,238
in fear that my dear daughter would
be caught in political mudslinging.

509
00:28:01,262 --> 00:28:04,048
Dad!

510
00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:13,015
Dad.

511
00:28:15,777 --> 00:28:17,937
What happened to you?

