676
00:39:16,437 --> 00:39:18,513
It's true.

677
00:39:19,273 --> 00:39:20,792
You're right.

678
00:39:20,816 --> 00:39:23,253
<i>You barged into my home...</i>

679
00:39:23,277 --> 00:39:26,298
<i>wielding farm tools.</i>

680
00:39:26,322 --> 00:39:29,149
Then I suddenly went into labor.

681
00:39:29,200 --> 00:39:30,844
And you helped me deliver Kang-ho.

682
00:39:30,868 --> 00:39:32,554
Me too.

683
00:39:32,578 --> 00:39:33,597
That's right.

684
00:39:33,621 --> 00:39:36,782
- You were born in that room.
- Yes, Mi-joo too.

685
00:39:38,667 --> 00:39:42,162
Just like how we can't
predict when we'll be born,

686
00:39:42,380 --> 00:39:45,999
we can't predict when we'll die either.

687
00:39:46,133 --> 00:39:50,947
I'd like to thank you all...

688
00:39:50,971 --> 00:39:54,091
while I still have a healthy mind.

689
00:39:55,142 --> 00:39:56,870
People might say...

690
00:39:56,894 --> 00:40:01,348
I'm the most unfortunate woman.

691
00:40:01,982 --> 00:40:05,685
I lost both my husband and my parents.

692
00:40:05,945 --> 00:40:10,315
And then my son was seriously injured,
and I have an incurable illness.

693
00:40:10,616 --> 00:40:14,319
I doubt there's anyone
who's more unlucky than me.

694
00:40:17,164 --> 00:40:18,907
But you know what?

695
00:40:20,501 --> 00:40:26,331
Life is so fascinating and makes you grateful.

696
00:40:27,216 --> 00:40:30,252
When it takes one thing from you,

697
00:40:30,386 --> 00:40:34,631
it always replaces it with something else.

698
00:40:37,017 --> 00:40:39,454
Losing my parents...

699
00:40:39,478 --> 00:40:42,389
